OL,3,CEnd 'unnecessary suffering' caused by
OL,4,Ctwo-child benefit cap, SNP says
OL,6,FThe SNP has called for an end to the
OL,7,F"unnecessary suffering" caused by the
OL,8,Ftwo-child benefit cap seven years on
OL,9,Ffrom its introduction.
OL,11,FPrime Minister Rishi Sunak has been
OL,12,Furged to reflect on the damage critics
OL,13,Fsay the policy has caused to families
OL,14,Fand commit to scrapping it.
OL,16,FLabour has previously said it would
OL,17,Fnot commit to scrapping the benefit
OL,18,Funless it could be fully costed,
OL,19,Fhowever Sir Keir Starmer said his
OL,20,Fparty would look to implement the
OL,21,Fpolicy "more fairly".
